Reasoning: The paper deals with self-supervised learning for monocular depth estimation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture for representation learning, which involves leveraging pretrained semantic segmentation networks, indicating a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions a two-stage training process to overcome a common semantic bias on dynamic objects, which suggests a focus on robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper mentions improving upon the state of the art for self-supervised monocular depth prediction, indicating a focus on computer vision and image processing, which makes cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
